You didn&#39;t share the most important part of configuration related to client authentication. That is the group config of clusters and group config from your client. I anticipate, the problem is rooted there.

The default authentication compares group name on the member with username coming from the client. The username is filled by the client&#39;s group name (by default).

Check the [AuthenticationBaseMessageTask](https://github.com/hazelcast/hazelcast/blob/v3.11.1/hazelcast/src/main/java/com/hazelcast/client/impl/protocol/task/AuthenticationBaseMessageTask.java#L161-L166) code

``` java
    private AuthenticationStatus authenticate(UsernamePasswordCredentials credentials) {
        GroupConfig groupConfig = nodeEngine.getConfig().getGroupConfig();
        String nodeGroupName = groupConfig.getName();
        boolean usernameMatch = nodeGroupName.equals(credentials.getUsername());
        return usernameMatch ? AuthenticationStatus.AUTHENTICATED : AuthenticationStatus.CREDENTIALS_FAILED;
    }
```

